President Donald Trump has issued a proclamation recognizing National Farm Safety and Health Week. The proclamation acknowledges the important contributions that farmers, ranchers, and foresters make to the economy and emphasizes the need to ensure their safety and health. It highlights the physical demands and potential dangers of farming, citing statistics on work-related injuries and deaths in the agricultural sector. The proclamation calls for the integration of safe practices and technologies into agricultural production systems to protect farmers and their families. It designates September 16 to September 22, 2018, as National Farm Safety and Health Week and encourages Americans to reaffirm their dedication to farm safety and health. The proclamation also urges people to honor the agricultural heritage and express appreciation for the contributions and service of farmers, ranchers, and foresters.